Package edu.csueastbay.cs401.ejamdar

Class JamdarPong

java.lang.Object
edu.csueastbay.cs401.pong.Game
edu.csueastbay.cs401.ejamdar.JamdarPong
public class JamdarPong extends edu.csueastbay.cs401.pong.Game
JamdarPong will bring out the features for the Jamdar version of Pong. This class will have the methods needed to play JamdarPong and is a modification of the Pong class.
Version:
1.0
Author:
Eshaq Jamdar

  • Constructor Details

    • JamdarPong

      public JamdarPong(int victoryScore, double fieldWidth, double fieldHeight)
      Method addBall() will create a new puck with a width and height member variables that are a part of JamdarPong. The puck is then added to the screen.

      Method is ran from the Initializer of JamdarPong and will add a random amount of Pucks from 1-5.

      Parameters:
      victoryScore - victory score is a score that determines the winner of the game: int
      fieldHeight - height represents the height of the game screen
      fieldWidth - width represents width of game screen

    • playSound

      private void playSound(int sound)
      This method takes in an int representing the sound effect to be played and will use GameController's backgroundMusic method to play the sound.

      This method is ran any time the puck collides with a wall or any paddle. Sound effect 1 plays the point sound when a point is obtained by either player. Sound effect 2 will play the sound anytime the puck hits any colidable object.

      Parameters:
      sound - an int representing the sfx to be played
      See Also:
      • JamdarPong

    • keyPressed

      public void keyPressed(javafx.scene.input.KeyCode code)
      Method keyPressed(KeyCode) will override the keyPressed method from the Game class and provide control movement on the x and y axis.

      Method is ran everytime a keystroke is registered and will move a paddle in the appropriate direction for the specific paddle player. WASD is for paddle 1 and IKJL is for the 2nd. W represents up, s represents down, a represents left, and d represents rights. Ditto for IJKL.

      Overrides:
      keyPressed in class edu.csueastbay.cs401.pong.Game
      Parameters:
      code - key stroke representing ASCII value on keyboard
      See Also:
      • JamdarPong

    • move

      public void move()
      Method move() will be used within collision function and is an overridden method from the paddle class that will allow for movement handling for the paddles of playerOne and Two.

      Method will call move2(), a method from within Paddle that handles movement for the x and y axis, on both paddle instances and then goes through the list of pucks to check collision and allows the puck to move.

      Overrides:
      move in class edu.csueastbay.cs401.pong.Game
